# Daft Dev Sandbox

## First things first

Initialize completions and daft shell integration:

    source init

## Available commands

    help                     Show this guide
    help --env               Show currently-set sandbox DAFT_* and GIT_* env vars
    test-plan [name]         Open branch test plan in neovim (auto-detects branch)
    manual-test <scenario>   Run a manual test scenario interactively
    manual-test --list       List available scenarios
    show-test <scenario>     Show test steps and commands for a scenario
    setup-test <scenario>    Set up a test environment for manual exploration
    reset-test [name]        Reset a test environment to its initial state
    rebuild-daft             Rebuild daft and update symlinks
    reload-sandbox           Re-source .envrc and init (pick up config changes)
    reset-sandbox            Wipe and recreate the sandbox from scratch
    go-to-worktree           Open a shell in the worktree directory
    clean-sandbox            Remove this sandbox and return to the worktree

## Tips

- Tab-complete scenario names and flags after running `source init`
- Run `rebuild-daft` after making code changes to pick them up
- Run `manual-test --keep <scenario>` to keep the test environment for inspection
- The sandbox has an isolated git identity and config directory
README

